# The inline <style> and <script> blocks in index.html and 404.html are pinned
# by SHA-256 in their Content-Security-Policy (and mirrored in _headers). Those
# hashes were computed over LF bytes, so these files must check out with LF
# endings on every platform regardless of a contributor's core.autocrlf setting.
# A CRLF checkout would change the bytes and the browser would refuse to run the
# blocks: an unstyled page and a dead countdown, failing only on fresh clones.
*.html   text eol=lf
_headers text eol=lf
